name: Jason Miyares
tweet: An absolute honor to speak at the Conference on Violent Crime this morning. Thank you to our law enforcement, victim advocates & public safety officials for all that you do.   My office is looking forward to working with you to create a safer Virginia.  https://t.co/UW0bb9X1xM

name: Jason Miyares
tweet: So great to be part of a VB tradition and kick off the @ShamrockOn Marathon with @GovernorVA.   As I told the crowd, welcome to Virginia Beach, the City of Heroes - enjoy the sunrise and stay for the sunsets!  https://t.co/GNHBKKCILu

name: Jason Miyares
tweet: Thank you to Alvey Elementary in Prince William County for having me today!   In honor of #ReadAcrossAmerica Month, we read a book about kindness.  https://t.co/9B9Gy7TB87

name: Jason Miyares
tweet: Our office is joining the Legal Food Frenzy competition this year to raise support for food banks. Today, I got to visit a participating food bank in Prince William County @ACTSPWC.   They’re doing phenomenal work serving families in need.    https://t.co/yZScBY9ppt  https://t.co/ZMEzZLnQE2

name: Jason Miyares
tweet: Thank you to Sheriff Decatur and everyone at @staffcosheriff for welcoming me today.   It was great talking about your service to the community and how we can work together to improve public safety.  https://t.co/adzJq52goQ

name: Jason Miyares
tweet: Another example of "progressive" prosecutors' pro-criminal policies. These murders should have been prevented.   Fairfax CA @SteveDescano had the chance and failed. Reduced charges/light sentences for dangerous offenders is not progressive, but regressive.

name: Jason Miyares
tweet: Law enforcement put everything on the line to protect our families and communities, without a second thought.  Yesterday, we tragically lost a law enforcement hero in the line of duty. Please join me in praying for the fallen Covington Officer, his family, and their community.
